Los Angeles Lakers star Kobe Bryant has admitted that the thought of retiring after this season has crossed his mind.

Bryant currently has another 12 months to run on a two-year contract extension he signed with the Western Conference franchise back in 2013, worth £32million.

When asked whether he has considered retiring after this season, Bryant nodded and told a Los Angeles Times report, 'I'd be lying if I said that it hasn't crossed my mind. Right now I doubt it... but anything's possible.'

