'My body is hurting like crazy, around the clock, and if I don't want to do this anymore, I won't do it,' he said.

The 36-year-old endured a nightmare campaign with the Lakers last year as a knee injury in December curtailed his involvement for the remainder of the season - while his side failed to reach the play-offs.

The 16-time All-Star guard has since made a complete recovery and, under head coach Byron Scott, has played in 34 of Los Angeles' 41 games - sitting some out to rest.

