If the five-time NBA champion were to retire and leave the Staples Center this season, he would waiver away £16.5m from his contract.

Bryant is averaging 22.6 points, 5.7 assists and 5.6 rebounds this season in 34.6 minutes per game.

The Lakers sit second bottom in the Western Conference standings with an undesirable win-loss record of 12-29 ahead of their trip to the Phoenix Suns in their next fixture on Monday night.

